{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780738218896,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_wJwo15ytrPOiF5dI60URMysg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"feedback.*(search_shown|result_cited|query_reformulated|same_topic_requery|follow_on_tool_use)|search_shown|result_cited","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit","include":"*.{md,ts,js,json}"},"output":"Found 52 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/manual_testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook.md:\n  Line 3198: Prompt: `Test the default-on SPECKIT_IMPLICIT_FEEDBACK_LOG behavior. Run a search, cite a result, reformulate the query, and verify the feedback ledger records events for all 5 types: search_shown, result_cited, query_reformulated, same_topic_requery, follow_on_tool_use. Confirm confidence tiers (strong/medium/weak) are correctly assigned and events are shadow-only. Return a concise user-facing pass/fail verdict with the main reason.`\n\n  Line 3200: 5 event types recorded; confidence tiers: strong (result_cited, follow_on_tool_use), medium (query_reformulated), weak (search_shown, same_topic_requery); shadow-only (no ranking influence)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md:\n  Line 2874: Enabled by default (graduated). Set `SPECKIT_IMPLICIT_FEEDBACK_LOG=false` to disable. The feedback ledger module records five event types with a three-tier confidence hierarchy: strong (result_cited, follow_on_tool_use), medium (query_reformulated), and weak (search_shown, same_topic_requery). Each event is stored with type, memory_id, query_id, confidence, timestamp, and optional session_id. Shadow-only: no ranking influence.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md:\n  Line 328: | `SPECKIT_IMPLICIT_FEEDBACK_LOG` | `true` | boolean | Implicit feedback event ledger for `search_shown`, `result_cited`, `query_reformulated`, `same_topic_requery`, and `follow_on_tool_use`. Event logging only, with no ranking side effects (REQ-D4-001). Graduated ON. | `lib/feedback/feedback-ledger.ts` |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts:\n  Line 50:   description: '[L2:Core] Search indexed spec-doc continuity semantically using vector similarity. Returns ranked results with similarity scores. Constitutional tier rules are ALWAYS included at the top of results (~2000 tokens max), regardless of query. Requires query (string), concepts (array of 2-5 strings), or cursor (string) for continuation pagination. Supports intent-aware retrieval (REQ-006) with task-specific weight adjustments. When implicit feedback logging is enabled, searches also emit shadow-only feedback signals such as search_shown and, for includeContent runs, result_cited. Token Budget: 3500. For code search, use mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query for structural code queries (callers, imports) and Grep for exact text or token searches.',\n\n  Line 103:         description: 'Include full file content in results. When true, each result includes a \"content\" field with the spec-doc file contents. This embeds load logic directly in search, eliminating the need for separate load calls. When implicit feedback logging is enabled, includeContent searches also emit shadow-only result_cited events for returned spec-doc records.'\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/memory-search.ts:\n  Line 1529:   // Implicit feedback — log search_shown events for returned results\n\n  Line 1548:             type: 'search_shown',\n\n  Line 1561:   // Query flow tracking + result_cited for includeC