() => {\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/vector-index-mutations.ts:\n  Line 176:       root_memory_id = excluded.root_memory_id,\n\n\n(Results truncated: showing 100 of 690 matches (590 hidden). Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":690,"truncated":true},"title":"Deprecated|deprecated|ARCHIVED|DORMANT|minState|includeArchived|hard-exclud|exclude","time":{"start":1780738218917,"end":1780738218987}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0374b68931204874016a23e8aa9c148191907d7f3d0fd46d9c"}},"id":"prt_e9c44db8c001TGEe391DLq9nDy","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","messageID":"msg_e9c44a35c001Mhg7LqeoFDDlDQ"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780738219553,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","part":{"id":"prt_e9c44de1d001cBYLGWqinoKay9","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"3c6638c09994ef54f19b1e3c5ebe6c7628286032","messageID":"msg_e9c44a35c001Mhg7LqeoFDDlDQ","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":124501,"input":15108,"output":310,"reasoning":27,"cache":{"write":0,"read":109056}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780738222238,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","part":{"id":"prt_e9c44e895001L7MF1NV7tFQgmC","messageID":"msg_e9c44e00a0015cI0ULRv7kjmAD","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","snapshot":"29538ace60dc4856bc376bfdbb990e4a3a34c8aa","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1780738257614,"sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","part":{"id":"prt_e9c451ff4001pvMZwrUrikTO24","messageID":"msg_e9c44e00a0015cI0ULRv7kjmAD","sessionID":"ses_163bcc502ffeLh3FDUFf5hqKPV","type":"text","text":"## Per-skill impact\n\n| Skill | What changes | Docs and/or code | UX/automation angle |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `system-spec-kit` | Largest impact. It owns Spec Kit Memory, MCP handlers, storage, search, feedback, env docs, save/index flows, and constitutional memory. Proposal `010` adds idempotency receipts, a tool-ownership map, and stale/status exclusion audit; amendments add `source_kind`, auto-cannot-overwrite-manual, advisory near-duplicate, tombstone/index rules, natural-key edge promotion, and the feedback reframe. | Docs and code. Update `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/memory_system.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save_workflow.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/README.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/README.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/README.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/storage/README.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/search/README.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/README.md`, and likely schema/handler code under `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`. | Automatic/invisible: receipt replay should be built into `memory_save` / `memory_update`, not exposed as a manual flag; stale-exclusion audit should run through health, validation, or scheduled diagnostics; feedback remains default-on event capture and shadow-only. UX: save/update responses should say “replayed existing write”, “advisory duplicate”, or “protected manual/constitutional field” clearly without requiring operators to inspect SQLite. |\n| `sk-doc` | Owns documentation quality for the new P2 MCP tool-ownership map and amended packet/spec-doc templates. It should enforce that ownership docs stay concise, current, and discoverable, without creating a new documentation workflow. | Mostly docs/templates. Relevant current docs are `.opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tools/README.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/memory_system.md`, and any new ownership-map doc under `system-spec-kit`. | Automatic/invisible: ownership-map generation or validation should derive from registered tool/schema metadata where possible, not hand-maintained tables. UX: the map should answer “which skill owns this tool group?” and “when may a tool be added/deprecated?” in one readable page. |\n| `sk-code` | Provides the OPENCODE TypeScript implementation surface and verification contract for the actual memory-server changes. It does not own requirements, but it must route implementation through MCP server authoring standards and targeted tests. | Mostly code-work guidance, likely no core `sk-code` docs change unless the MCP-server checklist needs a new reminder for idempotent writes, provenance guards, feedback shadow-only behavior, and search exclusion audits. Current contract is `.opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md`, especially OPENCODE detection and `assets/opencode/checklists/mcp_server_authoring.md`. | Automatic/invisible: verification should include targeted tests for retry replay, provenance overwrite blocking, advisory duplicate behavior, feedback no-side-effect guarantees, and default search inclusion. UX: failures should be surfaced as actionable handler/test messages, not silent ranking or mutation surprises. |\n| `system-skill-advisor` | Minimal impact. `source_kind` and feedback provenance are memory-row provenance, not skill-routing provenance. Advisor routing should not start ranking skills based on memory feedback events unless a separate measured routing packet exists. | Possibly docs-only if any routing brief needs to clarify that feedback/source provenance belongs to `system-spec-kit`, not advisor scoring. Current references are `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md` and its runtime/scoring docs. | Automatic/invisible: no new advisor path; existing hooks keep recommending `system-spec-kit`, `sk-doc`, or `sk-code` based on task intent. UX: if surfaced at all, briefs should say “memory provenance handled by system-spec-kit” rather than adding another operator decision. |\n\n## New skill needed?\n\nNo. This is hardening of an existing local memory system, not a new domain. `system-spec-kit` already owns Spec Kit Memory and MCP runtime behavior, `sk-doc` owns documentation quality, `sk-code` owns OPENCODE implementation/verification, and `system-skill-advisor` owns routing only.\n\n## Biggest-impact skill + why\n\n`system-spec-kit` has the biggest impact because every proposed behavior lands in or around its memory server: write idempotency, provenance enforcement, duplicate advisory, tombstones, causal-edge promotion, stale/default search behavior, feedback event capture, and MCP tool ownership.\n\nThe doc needing the most work is `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/memory_system.md`, with follow-on updates to `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md`, `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/README.md`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/README.md`.\n\nDELTA_JSON: {\"iteration\":\"002\",\"focus\":\"impact on skills\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.74,\"impacts\":[\"system-spec-kit -> memory server docs+code hardening for idempotency/provenance/search/feedback/tool ownership\",\"sk-doc -> ownership-map and amended spec-doc documentation quality/templates\",\"sk-code -> OPENCODE TypeScript implementation and verification surface\",\"system-skill-advisor -> docs-only boundary clarification; no routing behavior change\"],\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/research/008-caura-memclaw-fleet-memory-teachings/sub-packet-proposals.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/memory_system.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/memory/save_workflow.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/ENV_REFERENCE.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/handlers/save/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/feedback/README.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-doc/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/sk-code/SKILL.md\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md\"]}","time":{"start":1780738236404,"end":1780738257607},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0e85e582fdeed510016a23e8bc428c8191a94f716b1c1ba5bf","phase":"final_answer"}}}}
